    "recap_headline": "University of Washington",
    "recap_text": "SEATTLE \u2013\nThe Huskies took the midweek matchup decisively on Tuesday, defeating Saint Martin's 13-1 in seven innings.\nWashington improves to 9-11 with the win. The Dawgs have now won eight of their last 10 games.\nThe Huskies started hot and didn't look back. The Diamond Dawgs plated five in the second inning, punctuated by a three-run blast from\nBraeden Terry\nto deep right field.\nIn the third inning, the Dawgs hung another five, this time in large part thanks to a\nJackson Hotchkiss\ngrand slam. It was the first bases-loaded bomb of the season for the Huskies.\nDespite starting in only eight games so far this season, Hotchkiss has four home runs, tied for the second most on the team. He's currently batting an outrageous .471 (20-74).\nWashington scored three more in the fifth to bring the run total to 13 for the game.\nDefensively, the Huskies pitchers were effective across the board, allowing just six hits and one run.\nJay Miller\nmade the start, giving up three hits and one run.\nJaxson Gore\nwas credited with the win, tossing 2.2 inning with just one hit allowed against six strikeouts.\nPeysen Sweeney\n,\nTyler Walker\n, and\nTommy Brandenburg\ncombined to pitch the final two frames. The trio struck out four batters to secure the run-rule victory.\nAlex Perason made his season debut in the victory and earned his first RBI as a Husky on a bases-loaded hit by pitch.\nThe Huskies are back in action this weekend in Big Ten play at USC, opening a three-game series on Friday night in Los Angeles.\nDAWG BITES\nWashington claimed a 13-1 victory in seven innings, the first run rule win of the season\nThe Huskies are 8-2 in their last 10 games. The two losses came by two runs against SDSU and one run against Ohio State\nJackson Hotchkiss\nhas four home runs after hitting a grand slam on Tuesday, the second most on the team despite only making eight starts. The sophomore is batting .471\nBraeden Terry\nalso added his second home run of the season in the game\nTerry leads the team with 22 total hits\nFor news, scores, highlights and more,\ndownload the Go Huskies app\non your mobile device. Follow @UW_Baseball\u00a0on\nInstagram\n,\nX\n,\nThreads\n, and\nFacebook\nand subscribe to\nUW Athletics on YouTube\nfor the latest on the Dawgs."
